          <lg n="1">
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-1" n="1">I<lb/>Once on a time, as old stories rehearse,</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-2" n="2">A friar would needs show his talent in Latin;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-3" n="3">But was sorely put to't in the midst of a verse,</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-4" n="4">Because he could find no word to come pat in.</l>
            <l rend="indent(2)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-5" n="5">|Then all in the place</l>
            <l rend="indent(2)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-6" n="6">|He left a void space,</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-7" n="7">And so went to bed in a desperate case.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-8" n="8">When behold the next morning, a wonderful riddle,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-9" n="9">He found it was strangely filled up in the middle.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-10" n="10"><lb/>CHO[RUS]_Let censuring critics then think what they list on't,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-11" n="11">Who would not write verses with such an assistant.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-12" n="12"><lb/>II_This put me the friar into an amazement;</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-13" n="13">For he wisely considered it must be a sprite,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-14" n="14">That came through the keyhole, or in at the casement,</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-15" n="15">And it needs must be one that could both read and write:</l>
            <l rend="indent(2)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-16" n="16">|Yet he did not know</l>
            <l rend="indent(2)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-17" n="17">|If it were friend or foe,</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-18" n="18">Or whether it came from above or below.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-19" n="19">How'er, it was civil in angel or elf,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-20" n="20">For he ne'er could have filled it so well of himself.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-21" n="21"><lb/>CHO. Let censuring <hi rend="italics">etc</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-22" n="22">om.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-23" n="23"><lb/>III_Even so Master Doctor had puzzled his brains</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-24" n="24">In making a ballad, but was at a stand,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-25" n="25">He had mixed little wit with a great deal of pains;</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-26" n="26">When he found a new help from invisible hand.</l>
            <l rend="indent(2)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-27" n="27">|Then good Dr Swift</l>
            <l rend="indent(2)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-28" n="28">|Pay thanks for the gift,</l>
            <l rend="indent(1)" xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-29" n="29">For you freely must own you were at a dead lift;</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-30" n="30">And though some malicious young spirit did do't,</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-31" n="31">You may know by the <hi rend="italics">hand</hi>, it had no cloven <hi rend="italics">foot</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-32" n="32"><lb/>CHO. Let censuring <hi rend="italics">etc</hi>.</l>
            <l xml:id="swift-076-ROGP-line-33" n="33">om.</l>
          </lg>
